item.title: What is better?
item.dc:creator: @Natey Natey
item.description:
@Natey wrote:

well just like runescape would require a good source, but 317 is the best for noobies.

Think of it as this

Deltascape[317] = training wheels, barely riding.

Any 500+ source = getting the grip of riding, starting to ride better

Writing out your own source/server+ = you’re getting better

Writing out a source/server with good features and stability+ = pro.

Try learning basic java, I can get you some links, I’ll pm you them.

EDIT: basic conventions here http://java.sun.com/docs/codeconv/

Take a look, print it out too, just because that’s what I did and studied it and that’s how I got a grasp at programming.

item.title: What is better?
item.dc:creator: @Natey Natey
item.description:
@Natey wrote:

Depends, if you are new and want something easy, I’d say Deltascape source because it’s not packaged and it’s fairy simple to use.

If you already got a good grasp on coding then try a 508, thing is it’s packaged so a lot of stuff involved in doing minor updates.

I personally do 317 because I like old runescape, and my runescape account is nearly maxed so I can give 2 shits less about 500+
